<br>
i think it would make more sense to just make it do way less damage in pvp, for example, a VERY well geared wizard could do 1400-1500 tops with it, increase the cast time be 2-3 seconds, shorten the range, and have a 5-10 minute delay afterwards until they could use any of the instant abilities.  i figure that would be a decent compromise, they'd still be able to DT a small portion of casters who are fairly poorly geared, but it wouldn't be worth it since a few lures would have the same effect and leave them with more mana(thus getting rid of people who feel the need to be completely naked while doing it), and they would need to have a ton of mana to do it anyways.  the longer cast time/shorter range(not too short, but apx the range of bonds of force) would also add the option of running if the person saw it being cast near them.  the time it would take for them to instant gate would get rid of the problem where someone just kills, loots, and gates, long before the victim's group even realises that they were pked.  since the cap would only apply to pvp, none of this would even effect where it was meant to be used - pve, an extra 2-3 seconds cast time wouldn't matter, nor would the range issue or delay between instant gating.<br>
