Cyubkis- in my post I argued for changes similar to yours, I do think however, that 2-3 minutes of being unable to use your spellbar/instacast is very excessive.  Have manaburn do 70-90% of total hps assuming equal level and a full manabar for the wizard.  Also, no crit manaburn in pvp.  Then make it so using manaburn stuns the wizard for 7-10 seconds.  No instagate, mod-rods, conflag wands, pumice, nada, can't click them if you're stunned.  If you don't manage to kill your opponent, you're severely disabled, a necro will stack his dots, a melee will give you a friendly hug with his favorite 2-hander, and clerics will er...gate :P  If you're not at full mana when you cast manaburn, it does proportionate percentages of full hps based on your mana pool.  This forces wizards to not rely SOLELY on manaburn as a death-touch, which would bring it along-side harmtouch in terms of pvp power.  Lure, sunstrike, manaburn, 3 spells, not one 6-second casting deathtouch.  <br>
<br>
